`clap`-based argv parsing and report rendering for the `ctx-verify` binary — turns a `Report` into either the terse human render or the full JSON contract.

`CONTRACT` is a string constant with a load-bearing invariant: the `contracts` battery check (elsewhere in the checks/battery system) fails if the generated tool-contract block in `CLAUDE.md`/`README.md` drifts from this exact string — editing behavior here without updating those docs breaks CI.

`Cli` fields: `package` (optional `-p` scoping, cargo-only — doesn't scope the script battery), `max_diagnostics` (default 20, caps retained diagnostics per check), `checks` (comma-delimited allowlist of check names, empty = full default gate), `json` (switches output mode).

`run<R: Runner, W: Write>(runner: &R, cli: &Cli, out: &mut W) -> Result<bool, CheckError>` is the entry point: builds a `Report` via `checks::run_selected`, writes either JSON or terse output to `out`, and returns whether the overall status was `Pass`. Terse mode (`render_terse`) prints bare `pass` on success; otherwise emits one `FAIL:`/`ERROR:` block per non-passing, non-skipped check via `render_check`, with diagnostics locator-aligned (`file:line`, degrading to just `file` or `-`) and messages clipped to `MAX_MSG` (100 chars, ellipsis-terminated) — a `… +N more` tail appears when `check.truncated > 0`. JSON mode is untruncated/uncapped by this file (whatever `Report` serializes is emitted verbatim via `serde_json::to_writer_pretty`).

Depends on `checks::run_selected` and the `model` types (`Report`, `CheckReport`, `Diagnostic`, `Status`) for report shape, and `runner::Runner` as a trait-generic executor — this file only renders, it doesn't invoke cargo/rustc itself.